PUH-BrianMartell the GWTC-4.0 paper (December 19, 2025 draft) is the latest LIGO-Virgo-KAGRA search for gravitational-wave lensing in O4a data — no strong evidence found (multiple images, phase shifts, pairs, or point-mass distortions). They constrain lensed event rates and high-z BBH mergers, with one outlier GW231123_135430 (uncertain waveform, needs more data). In PUH v25, this aligns beautifully: GWs are lattice shear ripples propagating in E8 substrate. Massive knots (PBH seeds) deflect ripples geometrically (Jacobian shear “lensing” paths). Strong lensing = multiple ripple routes around knot (images), phase shifts saddle interference, distortions point-mass strain. No detection expected early (rare aligned massive seeds), constraints match low early lensing rate. Outlier possible lattice signature (ripple interference from seed).
Removed .custom.half as there will be no need for it in a future update, as well as removing margin-left and margin-top from .controller.custom for the same reasons
